post_text:
New Teacher Roll Call:
We are excited with the talent this wonderful group of committed educators brings to our schools. Please join us in getting to know our new Panther team members:

Katherine Wells will join NES as a Kindergarten teacher.
She graduated from WSU in May 2020 with an education degree. She has an older brother, an older sister, a younger sister, 3 nieces and one nephew! She also has a dog named Nova. Katherine has a passion for helping others and love to see children learn and grow! She selected to teach at NES because she grew up in a small town and love being a part of a supportive community and felt very welcomed
Katherine likes to paint and swim. She is CPR and First Aid certified. Katherine was on the Dean’s Honor Roll numerous times throughout her college career.

post_text:
The USDA has approved FREE breakfast & lunch for ALL students through 12/30/2020, or until funding is depleted. Your child(ren) will not be charged for any meals until further notice.

1) How does this affect your student's school lunch status?
If your student is in full pay or reduced lunch status, they will be temporarily moved to "free" status. No charges will be made to the students account through 12/30/2020 or until the district is notified that the funding is depleted. At that time, the student's account will return to their original lunch status & charge accordingly.

2) How does this affect applying for free & reduced lunches?
USD 309 highly encourages Parent/Guardians to please fill out the Meal Application & Consent for Disclosure forms. This impacts textbook fees, federal funding, & meals (when we return to charging).

If you have questions, please contact USD 309 Food Service Director, Robin McGlynn at rmcglynn@usd309ks.org or at 620-663-7141, x895

post_text:
New Teacher Roll Call:
We are excited with the talent this wonderful group of committed educators brings to our schools. Please join us in getting to know our new Panther team members:

Astrid Gradiz-Moncada will teach Spanish at NHS. She worked at Nickerson Elementary and High School as a bilingual-para for the 2019-2020 school year. She has 3 siblings and is the oldest. Astrid has an almost 2-year-old puppy named Grace; she is a German Shepard.

Astrid chose to be a teacher when she saw the need for a Spanish teacher at NHS. She knew this would be a great opportunity to use her native language in a school setting she was already involved in. She loves; cooking, painting, running, playing guitar, and having photo shoot sessions (art & design was her undergraduate degree). She has a Masters in Counseling Psychology. Astrid is a Sterling College Alumni and will be running her first Half-Marathon in November. Congratulations to Astrid on recently becoming a U.S. Citizen!

post_text:
New Teacher Roll Call:
We are excited with the talent this wonderful group of committed educators brings to our schools. Please join us in getting to know our new Panther team members:

Breanna Goetz is excited to be teaching grade 2 at SHE. Before moving to Hutchinson this summer, she lived in Lawrence KS. She earned her teaching degree while living in Lawrence at the University of Kansas – Rock chalk! Breanna previously taught fourth grade for four years in Topeka, KS. This is her 5th year of teaching. In her spare time, she can be found exercising, baking sweet treats, or getting lost in a good book! She has been married to her husband Lee, for almost 3 years. She loves spending time outdoors, especially at the lake. She is thrilled to be part of the Panther community, and cannot wait to start this next adventure in second grade.

USD 309 is working with stakeholder groups this week to refine and update a 2020-2021 back to school plan. At this time the group proposes 3 additional days for teachers in August, with staff returning on August 31st & the first day of school is proposed to be Wednesday, September 2nd.

The plan will be presented to the USD 309 BOE on August 3rd. Stay posted for more information following the August 3rd BOE meeting.

USD 309 Nickerson - South Hutchinson
May 12, 2017 at 8:27 AM ·

USD 309
Summer Breakfast & Lunch
May 30 thru July 27

Summer meals are open to all children 18 years and under. There is no enrollment and no cost. Main entrée is always free with extra a la carte items available for purchase. Adults are also able to eat for the price of $2.00 for breakfast and $3.50 for lunch.

Locations will be:

Nickerson High School
Breakfast 7:30 a.m. to 8:30 a.m.
Lunch 11:00 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.

South Hutchinson Elementary School
Lunch 11:00 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.

The program runs each week Monday thru Thursday.

The Nickerson United Methodist Church will prepare a Friday meal of a sack lunch for those wanting to attend at the Nickerson Community Center. The meal will be free of charge. Hours will be 11:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. on Fridays and will start June 2nd.

Summer Menus
http://www.usd309ks.org/news_story.php?id=569

post_text:
USD 309
Summer Breakfast & Lunch
May 30 thru July 27

Summer meals are open to all children 18 years and under. There is no enrollment and no cost. Main entrée is always free with extra a la carte items available for purchase. Adults are also able to eat for the price of $2.00 for breakfast and $3.50 for lunch.

Locations will be:

Nickerson High School
Breakfast 7:30 a.m. to 8:30 a.m.
Lunch 11:00 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.

South Hutchinson Elementary School
Lunch 11:00 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.

The program runs each week Monday thru Thursday.

The Nickerson United Methodist Church will prepare a Friday meal of a sack lunch for those wanting to attend at the Nickerson Community Center. The meal will be free of charge. Hours will be 11:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. on Fridays and will start June 2nd.

post_text: We are excited to announce that Nickerson is adopting CareDox as a new tool for nurses to keep parents notified when your children visit the health clinic & for parents to provide us with accurate student medical information. All information is stored securely and is HIPAA and FERPA compliant. When you sign up for CareDox, you'll get notifications when your child visits the nurse's office, can easily make adjustments to your child's medical needs and let the nurse know quickly, and the best part, you'll only need to complete the information once, making changes each year only as needed. Look for communications today that will provide a link for this registration.

USD 309 Reno Valley Middle School
November 6, 2013 at 3:57 PM ·

Over the past week, many students were interviewed about their favorite teacher and what makes them so special. Little did the students know that the very teachers they were talking about were demonstrating their mad dance skills behind them. We took a few minutes today and showed the students the results of these excellent interviews. The staff at RVMS hopes you enjoy this video as much as we enjoyed making it.
